Pasadena and Deer Park fire fighters were able to extinguish a house fire Wednesday despite a few challenges, Pasadena Fire Marshal David Brannon said. 
Crews responded to the emergency call at about noon on Feb. 8 at 4010 Willowview in Pasadena. 
TORNADOES: Louisiana mom clings to baby during storms 
Fire became trapped in hidden spaces in the home's attic, Brannon said. No injuries were reported and the blaze was extinguished about two hours later. 
In photos and video, smoke and flames can be seen over the roof near the rear of the home. 
The cause of the fire is not known at this time. 
Kar Hlava
